   {
      "body" : "Instead, it would be better to add BIP32 support, and other features which make it easier to avoid address reuse as an opt-in features, rather than nagging people about address reuse.\r\n\r\nThere is nothing invalid about address reuse on a protocol level.\r\n\r\nThe politics of address reuse need to stay out of the bitcoin core functionality.\r\n\r\nProactively pushing an agenda and trying to convince people that bitcoin fungibility is not universal when reusing addresses is a slippery slope indeed.",
